    Class Description
    CalendarPicker
    This class definition was modified from the example published on this page: https://blog.eduonix.com/java-programming-2/how-to-use-date-picker-component-in-java/
    Client
    Creates a client object of name and id, There are other methods that are related to the client and lease classes such as add new lease, list lease, cancel lease and cancel lease with a specific confirmation number.
    ConferenceRoom
    Conference Room to be rented.
    DuplicateClientException
    DuplicateClientException class when there are duplicate clients
    DuplicateRoomException
    DuplicateRoomException class when there are duplicate rooms
    HotelSuite
    Hotel Suite to be rented.
    Landlord
    Landlord describes behaviors that the back end (model) must support for a front end (user interface) of the Wolf High-Rise Rental Application.
    Lease
    Lease class which manages the creation of a Lease object, and creates a valid lease using the client and rental unit package information
    Office
    Office space to be rented, maintains a calendar.
    PropertyManager
    This class follows the Singleton pattern which is "implemented through a private constructor and the method ProjectManager.getInstance(), which returns the only instance of ProjectManager." and the factory pattern which is "implemented through the method ProjectManager.addNewUnit() and the RentalUnit class hierarchy.
    RentalCapacityException
    RentalCapacityException to be thrown when rental capacity is invalid
    RentalDateException
    RentalDateException to be thrown when the rental data is invalid
    RentalGUI
    Graphical user interface for the Wolf High-Rise Rental system.
    RentalOutOfServiceException
    RentalOutOfServiceException to be thrown when a rental unit is out a service
    RentalReader
    This class reads Rental Data files and adds data from file to PropertyManager fields
    RentalUnit
    Abstract class of rental unit, is extended by all of the other possible rental units.
    RentalWriter
    Writes rental data to a file
    SimpleArrayList<E>
    Array List for storing objects
    SimpleList<E>
    A simple generic list (ordered collection) interface adapted from java.util.List.
    SimpleListIterator<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
    Represents a cursor into a list that can move forward.
    SortedLinkedListWithIterator<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
    Sorted Linked List with an Iterator to store elements
    SortedList<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
    This interface is a subset of the java.util.List interface and requires that elements be stored in sorted order based on Comparable.
    SpringUtilities
    A 1.4 file that provides utility methods for creating form- or grid-style layouts with SpringLayout.
